It's cancer.

310
00:16:37,126 --> 00:16:40,085
- You're--you're gonna be okay,
right?

311
00:16:40,129 --> 00:16:42,348
You're gonna be okay?

312
00:16:42,392 --> 00:16:44,263
- We're gonna get through
this together, Junior.

313
00:16:46,091 --> 00:16:47,484
Please don't worry.

314
00:16:51,314 --> 00:16:54,099
Come here, buddy.

315
00:16:54,143 --> 00:16:55,796
Come here.

316
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,189
Oh.

317
00:17:01,106 --> 00:17:03,152
I love you, buddy.

318
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:09,158
Oh, my boy.

319
00:17:10,420 --> 00:17:13,031
You ready? Look. Huh?

320
00:17:15,338 --> 00:17:18,341
I guess today
is my lucky day, huh?

321
00:17:18,384 --> 00:17:20,125
[laughs]

322
00:17:20,169 --> 00:17:21,996
Funny.

323
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:24,260
I don't remember you
being dumb enough

324
00:17:24,303 --> 00:17:26,175
to chase an inside straight,

325
00:17:26,218 --> 00:17:28,786
even if you are lucky enough
to get it.

326
00:17:28,829 --> 00:17:30,135
[laughs]

327
00:17:30,179 --> 00:17:31,919
Another beer?

328
00:17:31,963 --> 00:17:33,312
No, I'm okay.

329
00:17:33,356 --> 00:17:35,053
- Ah, cuttin' back,
are you, Chucky?

330
00:17:40,363 --> 00:17:44,410
You know what this motel
reminds me of?

331
00:17:44,454 --> 00:17:49,154
It reminds me
of that night in Niagara.

332
00:17:49,198 --> 00:17:53,158
- All those fond memories.
- [laughs]

333
00:17:53,202 --> 00:17:56,161
It's why I chose this dump.

334
00:17:56,205 --> 00:17:58,946
Tell me, do you
remember Niagara, Chucky?

335
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:03,168
- You know, I'm more of
a live-in-the-present

336
00:18:03,212 --> 00:18:04,474
kinda guy, huh?

337
00:18:04,517 --> 00:18:06,215
Humor me.

338
00:18:06,258 --> 00:18:08,347
What was your favorite part?

339
00:18:12,177 --> 00:18:13,483
Come on, Tiff.

340
00:18:13,526 --> 00:18:15,093
That was a long time ago.

341
00:18:15,137 --> 00:18:16,399
Raise you 100.

342
00:18:16,442 --> 00:18:18,836
I call.

343
00:18:18,879 --> 00:18:23,057
Too long to remember
your own honeymoon, Chucky?

344
00:18:23,101 --> 00:18:24,407
Come on.

345
00:18:26,931 --> 00:18:31,370
- You know, my favorite part
was just being with you.

346
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:36,288
Aww, shucks.

347
00:18:36,332 --> 00:18:38,986
- [laughs]
- I never figured you to be

348
00:18:39,030 --> 00:18:42,207
the sentimental type, Chucky.

349
00:18:42,251 --> 00:18:44,166
- I'm all-in.

350
00:18:44,209 --> 00:18:46,472
- All right. I'm all-in too.

351
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:55,525
[chuckles]

352
00:18:57,483 --> 00:18:59,137
Hello, Nica.

353
00:19:02,619 --> 00:19:05,883
Long time no see.

354
00:19:07,972 --> 00:19:10,409
Nica? I'm not Nica.

355
00:19:10,453 --> 00:19:11,454
Why do you think I'm Nica?
I'm not--

356
00:19:11,497 --> 00:19:13,325
I'm not--

357
00:19:13,369 --> 00:19:16,328
<i>[tense music]</i>

358
00:19:16,372 --> 00:19:23,248
<i>♪ </i>

359
00:19:23,292 --> 00:19:25,250
Is it Chucky doesn't bluff?

360
00:19:25,294 --> 00:19:28,253
Ohh, Chucky bluffs.

361
00:19:28,297 --> 00:19:31,604
But he doesn't chew
on his fingernails.

362
00:19:31,648 --> 00:19:34,346
[laughs]

363
00:19:34,390 --> 00:19:38,568
Besides, I stabbed you
in the thigh ten minutes ago.

364
00:19:38,611 --> 00:19:41,266
You didn't feel a thing.

365
00:19:41,310 --> 00:19:43,007
Ooh, if it'd have been Chucky,

366
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,444
he woulda screamed
like a banshee.

367
00:19:45,488 --> 00:19:48,839
But not you,
being paralyzed and all.

368
00:19:53,278 --> 00:19:55,019
What are you gonna do to me?

369
00:19:55,062 --> 00:19:57,587
- I don't know.
that's an interesting question.

370
00:19:57,630 --> 00:20:00,981
You see, the thing is, Nica,

371
00:20:01,025 --> 00:20:04,289
I spent some with you,
I spent some time with Chucky,

372
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:06,204
and I gotta say,

373
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:07,858
I like you better.

374
00:20:08,641 --> 00:20:10,295
[chuckles]

375
00:20:10,339 --> 00:20:12,036
You do?

376
00:20:12,079 --> 00:20:14,256
Do you wanna know a secret?

377
00:20:16,388 --> 00:20:17,607
Sure.

378
00:20:20,131 --> 00:20:24,178
- Sometimes,
when we're together, I--

379
00:20:24,222 --> 00:20:27,573
I see you looking at me,

380
00:20:27,617 --> 00:20:30,141
and I know it's you.

381
00:20:30,184 --> 00:20:35,320
It's not Chucky,
it's you, and...

382
00:20:35,364 --> 00:20:37,148
I live for those moments.

383
00:20:39,063 --> 00:20:42,327
I want to have those moments
all the time.

384
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:45,896
- Mm-hmm.
- I--[sighs]

385
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:50,204
Guess what?

386
00:20:50,248 --> 00:20:53,077
I have a surprise
for you, Nica.

387
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,384
I bought us a house

388
00:20:55,427 --> 00:20:59,039
right here in Hackensack.

389
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:03,217
You know, they say the saints
look over everybody

390
00:21:03,261 --> 00:21:05,350
that lives in Hackensack,

391
00:21:05,394 --> 00:21:11,182
even non-traditional couples
like ourselves.

392
00:21:11,225 --> 00:21:16,405
The only problem is...

393
00:21:16,448 --> 00:21:19,103
How do I keep you
in the driver's seat

394
00:21:19,146 --> 00:21:22,019
- instead of that rat Chucky?
- [laughs]

395
00:21:25,457 --> 00:21:28,199
[humming]

396
00:21:28,242 --> 00:21:29,679
Ahh!

397
00:21:37,034 --> 00:21:38,557
He's not on Insta.

398
00:21:39,166 --> 00:21:40,733
Not on Snap.

399
00:21:40,777 --> 00:21:43,562
Not on Twitter.

400
00:21:43,606 --> 00:21:46,957
- Well...
- What?

401
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,480
- I Googled Andy Barclay and
got an article

402
00:21:48,524 --> 00:21:50,090
from two weeks ago.

403
00:21:50,134 --> 00:21:53,659
"Violent Patient Escapes
Harrogate Psychiatric Hospital

404
00:21:53,703 --> 00:21:55,052
Manhunt Underway"

405
00:21:55,966 --> 00:21:58,882
[sighs] Great sign.

406
00:21:58,925 --> 00:22:00,274
[doorbell dings]

407
00:22:00,318 --> 00:22:02,755
Be right back.

408
00:22:02,799 --> 00:22:05,541
- Wait, Harrogate,
where is that?

409
00:22:05,584 --> 00:22:08,935
- Rhode Island.
- Rhode Island?

410
00:22:08,979 --> 00:22:12,286
Wait, I got a call from Rhode
Island about a month ago.

411
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:13,984
Holy shit,
that must be Andy Barclay.

412
00:22:18,292 --> 00:22:20,294
God.

413
00:22:20,338 --> 00:22:25,256
Junior, I'm so sorry.

414
00:22:25,299 --> 00:22:27,780
- I just feel like everything's
falling apart right now,

415
00:22:27,824 --> 00:22:29,086
you know?

416
00:22:29,129 --> 00:22:33,917
My mom, my uncle.

417
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:35,092
Even you and me.

418
00:22:37,181 --> 00:22:41,141
No. No, not us.

419
00:22:41,185 --> 00:22:42,708
I'm always here for you.

420
00:22:42,752 --> 00:22:46,103
Hey, Lexy, he's on Facebook!

421
00:22:46,146 --> 00:22:48,497
- I just feel like you're
somewhere else these days.

422
00:22:50,847 --> 00:22:53,197
I'm sorry, what?

423
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,633
You see what I mean?

424
00:22:54,677 --> 00:22:56,330
The fuck, Lex?

425
00:22:56,374 --> 00:22:58,028
It's like I don't even
exist to you anymore!

426
00:22:59,203 --> 00:23:03,729
- No. No, that's--
that's not true.

427
00:23:03,773 --> 00:23:06,210
I'm always here for you.

428
00:23:06,253 --> 00:23:08,604
I love you.

429
00:23:08,647 --> 00:23:10,780
And it's like you said,
everything has just been

430
00:23:10,823 --> 00:23:12,782
such a mess lately,
and I just want to protect you.

431
00:23:12,825 --> 00:23:15,654
No.

432
00:23:15,698 --> 00:23:17,177
No?

433
00:23:17,221 --> 00:23:19,745
It's over.

434
00:23:19,789 --> 00:23:25,795
We're done.

435
00:23:25,838 --> 00:23:28,058
No.

436
00:23:28,101 --> 00:23:30,060
No, Junior, please.

437
00:23:30,103 --> 00:23:31,975
Please don't do this.
We can fix this.

438
00:23:32,018 --> 00:23:33,977
I just did.

439
00:23:37,284 --> 00:23:40,723
[door opens, shuts]

440
00:23:43,116 --> 00:23:45,379
- Wait, how old's
this guy again?

441
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:47,686
Um, 40.

442
00:23:47,730 --> 00:23:50,863
God help us.

443
00:23:50,907 --> 00:23:52,822
<i>- Hi. This is Andy Barclay. </i>
Leave a message.

444
00:23:52,865 --> 00:23:53,866
<i>[beep]</i>

445
00:23:53,910 --> 00:23:56,347
Shit.

446
00:23:56,390 --> 00:23:59,002
[phone ringing]

447
00:23:59,045 --> 00:24:00,177
- Uh--

448
00:24:02,135 --> 00:24:03,702
Andy Barclay?

449
00:24:03,746 --> 00:24:04,877
<i>Jake Wheeler.</i>

450
00:24:04,921 --> 00:24:06,923
Where are you?

451
00:24:06,966 --> 00:24:09,665
<i>In a kitchen in Hackensack.</i>

452
00:24:09,708 --> 00:24:11,884
Hackensack. Figures.

453
00:24:11,928 --> 00:24:14,713
- You know about Chucky,
and you're still alive.

454
00:24:14,757 --> 00:24:16,759
Makes you one of the lucky few.

455
00:24:16,802 --> 00:24:19,065
It's a shitty club to be in,
but welcome.

456
00:24:19,109 --> 00:24:20,893
<i>- At first I thought </i>
I was going crazy.

457
00:24:20,937 --> 00:24:22,155
- Well, you haven't told
anyone, have you?

458
00:24:22,199 --> 00:24:23,679
No. No one.

459
00:24:23,722 --> 00:24:25,681
- Look, you feel like
you're going crazy?

460
00:24:25,724 --> 00:24:28,814
That's exactly what everyone
will think if you tell them.

461
00:24:28,858 --> 00:24:31,774
Speaking of crazy, Chucky's
not with anyone, is he?

462
00:24:31,817 --> 00:24:33,732
A woman? Two women?

463
00:24:33,776 --> 00:24:34,951
- Uh--

464
00:24:34,994 --> 00:24:37,214
No, I don't think so, but

465
00:24:37,257 --> 00:24:39,782
listen, Andy, I have, like,
a million questions.

466
00:24:39,825 --> 00:24:42,132
We're out of time,
and we need your help.

467
00:24:42,175 --> 00:24:43,437
<i>How do we find him?</i>

468
00:24:43,481 --> 00:24:45,744
- Oh, you don't have
to find Chucky.

469
00:24:45,788 --> 00:24:47,180
He'll find you.

470
00:24:47,224 --> 00:24:48,921
<i>And if he can't find you,</i>

471
00:24:48,965 --> 00:24:51,663
<i>he'll go after your </i>
whole family to get to you.

472
00:24:51,707 --> 00:24:53,970
<i>- He killed </i>
our foster parents, Jake.

473
00:24:54,013 --> 00:24:55,798
<i>He'll stop at nothing.</i>

474
00:24:57,800 --> 00:25:00,759
- Oh, and Jake, it'll be
somewhere he's familiar with,

475
00:25:00,803 --> 00:25:02,369
<i>and you're </i>
at your most vulnerable.

476
00:25:02,413 --> 00:25:05,111
<i>That's exactly </i>
where he'll find you.

477
00:25:05,155 --> 00:25:06,243
Junior's house.

478
00:25:07,418 --> 00:25:09,812
- Not a bad place
to spring a trap.

479
00:25:09,855 --> 00:25:11,074
<i>Well, text me the address.</i>

480
00:25:11,117 --> 00:25:12,815
We're on our way.

481
00:25:12,858 --> 00:25:17,776
<i>♪ </i>

482
00:25:20,866 --> 00:25:22,955
[laughs]

483
00:25:22,999 --> 00:25:25,001
[humming]

484
00:25:27,525 --> 00:25:31,964
Gladys! Big day!

485
00:25:32,008 --> 00:25:35,968
- Congratulations, Miss Tilly.
- Thank you. Thank you.

486
00:25:36,012 --> 00:25:37,927
- Well, you know, the house
has beautiful bones.

487
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:40,494
- Mm-hmm.
- It just needs a little TLC.

488
00:25:40,538 --> 00:25:42,845
- Mm-hmm.
- And someone like yourself...

489
00:25:42,888 --> 00:25:44,977
- Yes.
- With a vision to restore it

490
00:25:45,021 --> 00:25:47,197
to its mid-century glory.

491
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:51,331
- Yes. We have big plans
for this place.

492
00:25:51,375 --> 00:25:53,203
- We?
- Yes.

493
00:25:53,246 --> 00:25:56,293
Me and my fiancée
will be moving in immediately.

494
00:25:56,336 --> 00:25:59,818
- Oh, congratulations!
That's wonderful!

495
00:25:59,862 --> 00:26:00,906
Thank you. Yes.

496
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:02,429
- What brings you
to Hackensack?

497
00:26:02,473 --> 00:26:05,258
- Well, my fiancée
grew up here, actually.

498
00:26:05,302 --> 00:26:07,173
Right in this very house.

499
00:26:07,217 --> 00:26:09,045
- Oh!
- Mm-hmm.

500
00:26:09,088 --> 00:26:14,267
- I--it's just been empty
ever since--

501
00:26:14,311 --> 00:26:18,097
- Ever since the murders.
Yes.

502
00:26:18,141 --> 00:26:20,534
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

503
00:26:20,578 --> 00:26:24,016
- Oh, so it was
your fiancée's parents that--

504
00:26:24,060 --> 00:26:27,280
[laughs] Yes. Yes.

505
00:26:27,324 --> 00:26:29,543
So many memories.

506
00:26:29,587 --> 00:26:33,852
- Okay. You know,
I almost forgot.

507
00:26:33,896 --> 00:26:35,419
You've already started
getting some mail.

508
00:26:35,462 --> 00:26:37,900
Oh! [gasps]

509
00:26:37,943 --> 00:26:40,337
Oh!

510
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:41,773
There you go.

511
00:26:41,817 --> 00:26:43,949
- I have an online
shopping addiction.

512
00:26:43,993 --> 00:26:47,387
- Okay. Well, you have
a good night, Miss Tilly.

513
00:26:47,431 --> 00:26:49,781
- Oh, would you
like my autograph?

514
00:26:49,825 --> 00:26:51,217
Next time!

515
00:26:51,261 --> 00:26:53,176
Okay.

516
00:26:53,219 --> 00:26:56,135
Weirdo.

517
00:26:56,179 --> 00:26:58,442
[humming]

518
00:27:00,444 --> 00:27:04,578
I'll put you
right here for now.

519
00:27:04,622 --> 00:27:06,450
And...

520
00:27:06,493 --> 00:27:11,890
<i>♪ </i>

521
00:27:11,934 --> 00:27:14,545
[whimpering softly]

522
00:27:14,588 --> 00:27:17,504
Welcome home!

